  <div id="education-panel" class="absolute bottom-4 right-4 info-panel p-4 z-20" style="width: 300px;">
   <h3 class="text-sm font-bold mb-2 glow-text" style="font-family: 'Orbitron', sans-serif; color: #64d2ff;">🎓 Orbital Mechanics</h3>
   <div id="education-content" class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: #a0c4ff;">
    <p class="mb-2"><strong style="color: #64d2ff;">Kepler's Laws:</strong> Planets orbit in ellipses with the Sun at one focus. They sweep equal areas in equal times.</p>
    <p><strong style="color: #64d2ff;">Current View:</strong> <span id="current-fact">Earth completes one orbit in 365.25 days, traveling at ~107,000 km/h.</span></p>
   </div>
